# youchop.app — server env (set these in the Vercel project, not committed)
# The "Channel → Text" tool (/extract) uses two FREE backends:

# 1) Channel search + video listing — YouTube Data API v3 (FREE, 10,000 units/day).
#    Create a key: Google Cloud Console → enable "YouTube Data API v3" → Credentials → API key.
#    No billing required for the free quota. search costs 100 units, listing ~1 unit / 50 videos.
YT_DATA_API_KEY=

# 2) Transcripts — two FREE providers; if both are set they form a fallback chain
#    (apify → supadata → ytio): when one is capped for the month, the next takes over.
#
#    a) Apify (FREE tier: $5/mo credits, ~$0.007/video). Runs the scrape on Apify's
#       infra, so it survives YouTube's datacenter-IP blocking that kills direct
#       scraping on Vercel. Token: apify.com → Settings → API & Integrations.
#       Default actor: karamelo/youtube-transcripts. Override with APIFY_TRANSCRIPT_ACTOR.
APIFY_TOKEN=
# APIFY_TRANSCRIPT_ACTOR=karamelo~youtube-transcripts
#
#    b) Supadata (FREE: 100 transcripts/mo, no credit card). dash.supadata.ai → API key.
SUPADATA_API_KEY=

# Optional overrides:
# TRANSCRIPT_PROVIDER=apify        # force one provider: "apify" | "supadata" | "ytio"

# Optional PAID fallback — youtube-transcript.io (Plus $9.99/mo). Only used if TRANSCRIPT_PROVIDER=ytio
# or if APIFY_TOKEN is absent. Paste ONLY the token (code prepends "Basic ").
YT_TRANSCRIPT_TOKEN=
